						               													<description>The players are reporters for a school magazine and try to catch the newest &amp;bdquo;title story&amp;ldquo; for it.&amp;#10;So they chase through the city trying to be the first.&amp;#10;The game comes with two game modes.&amp;#10;1. players play clockwise and either collect cards or play them and collect tokens from the board matching the color of the blueprint of their story. When one of the three parts of the story is full, they look at the card for ca. 30 seconds and try to memorize as much as possible.&amp;#10;They are asked a question in the vein of &amp;bdquo;what is the kid in the background eating?&amp;ldquo; and if they guess it right they keep the card.&amp;#10;The first to collect enough tokens and to answer the three cards correctly wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2. there are 8 decks of cards available and the players take a deck and search for cards that point in the right direction in their own player color, they program simultaneously their path through the city and try to get to the colored tokens. In player order they check if they collect enough tokens to try to answer a question.&amp;#10;When all three cards are fulfilled the player who has all three cards in front of himself wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
